    "Sure",
    ", here",
    "'s a quick",
    " primer on",
    " Kotlin coroutines",
    ":\n\n",
    "**Core idea**",
    "\n\n",
    "A coroutine is",
    " a *suspendable*",
    " computation. It",
    " can pause",
    " (`suspend`) without",
    " blocking",
    " its underlying",
    " thread, then resume",
    " later — possibly",
    " on a different",
    " thread.\n\n",
    "**Building blocks**",
    "\n\n",
    "- `suspend fun`",
    " — declares a",
    " function that",
    " can suspend.\n",
    "- `CoroutineScope`",
    " — owns a set of",
    " coroutines and their",
    " lifetime.\n",
    "- `launch`",
    " — fire-and-forget",
    ".\n",
    "- `async`",
    " — produces",
    " a `Deferred<T>`",
    " result.\n",
    "- `withContext`",
    " — switches",
    " dispatcher",
    " for a block.\n\n",
    "**Tiny example**",
    "\n\n",
    "```kotlin\n",
    "suspend fun fetchUser(): User =\n",
    "    withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {\n",
    "        api.getUser()\n",
    "    }\n",
    "```\n\n",
    "**Why it matters**",
    "\n\n",
    "Structured concurrency",
    " (job hierarchies",
    " + cancellation propagation",
    ") makes",
    " async code easier",
    " to reason about",
    " than raw threads",
    " or callbacks."
